<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-20T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-20T16:00:00-05:00" n="496" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123J634/359: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-20T17:00:00-04:00">August 20, 1935—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>254. The appointed Chinese Ambassador is to present his letters of
                            credence to the President on August 21.</p>
                        <p>Due to the fact that the President expects to leave Washington in the
                            near future and the date of his return is uncertain, it has seemed
                            impracticable to endeavor to arrange that the Chinese Ambassador present
                            his letters of credence on approximately the date set for you to present
                            your letters of credence.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>